article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 62, Cal St.-Fullerton 61
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Denzel Barnes nailed two free throws with one second left to hoist Stephen F. Austin to a 62-61 victory over Cal State-Fullerton and a win in the Etech Lumberjack Classic on Saturday night. Barnes, who came off the bench to score 10 points for the Lumberjacks (5-2), made the game-winning shots after the Titans (3-2) took the lead in the final minute with a 3-pointer from Orane Chin and a pair of free throws by Jacques Streeter. The Lumberjacks' Walt Harris led the game in scoring with 20 points, while teammate Jordan Glynn had a double-double, scoring 13 points and pulling down 10 rebounds. Jer'Vaughn Johnson scored eight of his team-leading 13 points in the second half, including hitting each of his six of his seven points the line. Steeter, Aaron Thompson and Devon Peltier each added 11 points for the Titans.
